dcterms:description: CAMI2 is a comprehensive benchmark designed to mimic realistic microbiome environments, including a vast array of both new and known genomes, as well as plasmids and viruses, providing a robust evaluation for DNA embedding models.
dcterms:title: CAMI2

dcterms:description: GenBank is a comprehensive public database of nucleotide sequences and their protein translations, providing a vast resource for genomic research.
dcterms:title: GenBank

dcterms:description: Synthetic datasets are created by randomly extracting DNA sequences from reference genomes, used for evaluating model performance in various tasks.
dcterms:title: Synthetic datasets

dcterms:description: Marine datasets consist of long-read contigs from marine environments, containing DNA sequences belonging to various species sampled from microbial genomes.
dcterms:title: Marine datasets

dcterms:description: Plant datasets include long-read contigs from plant-associated environments, containing DNA sequences from various species sampled from microbial genomes.
dcterms:title: Plant datasets

dcterms:description: Fungi datasets consist of long-read contigs from fungal environments, containing DNA sequences belonging to various species sampled from microbial genomes.
dcterms:title: Fungi datasets

dcterms:description: Viral datasets consist of long-read contigs from viral environments, containing DNA sequences belonging to various species sampled from microbial genomes.
dcterms:title: Viral datasets
